## Link to this sectionModelos personalizados#

This example loads a custom 20-class [VOC](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov5/blob/master/data/VOC.yaml)-trained YOLOv5s model `'best.pt'` with PyTorch Hub.
    
    
    import torch
    
    model = torch.hub.load("ultralytics/yolov5", "custom", path="path/to/best.pt")  # local model
    model = torch.hub.load("path/to/yolov5", "custom", path="path/to/best.pt", source="local")  # local repo

## Link to this sectionModelos TensorRT, ONNX e OpenVINO#

O PyTorch Hub suporta inferência na maioria dos formatos de exportação YOLOv5, incluindo modelos treinados personalizados. Veja o [tutorial de Exportação TFLite, ONNX, CoreML, TensorRT](/pt/yolov5/tutorials/model-export) para detalhes sobre a exportação de modelos.

Dica

  * **TensorRT** pode ser 2-5× mais rápido que o PyTorch em [benchmarks de GPU](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov5/pull/6963).
  * **ONNX** e **OpenVINO** podem ser 2-3× mais rápidos que o PyTorch em [benchmarks de CPU](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov5/pull/6613).


    
    
    import torch
    
    model = torch.hub.load("ultralytics/yolov5", "custom", path="yolov5s.pt")  # PyTorch
    model = torch.hub.load("ultralytics/yolov5", "custom", path="yolov5s.torchscript")  # TorchScript
    model = torch.hub.load("ultralytics/yolov5", "custom", path="yolov5s.onnx")  # ONNX
    model = torch.hub.load("ultralytics/yolov5", "custom", path="yolov5s_openvino_model/")  # OpenVINO
    model = torch.hub.load("ultralytics/yolov5", "custom", path="yolov5s.engine")  # TensorRT
    model = torch.hub.load("ultralytics/yolov5", "custom", path="yolov5s.mlmodel")  # CoreML (macOS-only)
    model = torch.hub.load("ultralytics/yolov5", "custom", path="yolov5s.tflite")  # TFLite
    model = torch.hub.load("ultralytics/yolov5", "custom", path="yolov5s_paddle_model/")  # PaddlePaddle

